Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.03,0:00:03.74,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,I feel it...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.63,0:00:09.92,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,An evil spirit is approaching, \Nfilled with anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.92,0:00:11.62,Bengoshi-Top,K,0,0,0,,An evil spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.52,0:00:13.93,Bengoshi-Credits_Left,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Hakamada's assistant:\N Nonomura Kanae
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.62,0:00:13.25,Bengoshi-Top,K,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.02,0:00:23.73,Default,K,0,0,0,,What? Are you talking about Misato-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.43,0:00:25.00,Bengoshi-Credits_Right,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Editor at Tokiwa Publishing: \NTabata Misato
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.46,0:00:26.77,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,Kanae-san, sorry I'm late.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.77,0:00:29.97,Default,K,0,0,0,,She's not angry at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.97,0:00:32.81,Bengoshi-Credits,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Cafe waitress:\N Mizutani Sara
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.97,0:00:32.81,Bengoshi-Top,Sara,0,0,0,,No, I am never wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.81,0:00:35.85,Default,K,0,0,0,,As far as I know, you've always \Ngotten our orders wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.85,0:00:40.12,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,I brought someone who wants\N to meet you, Kanae-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.12,0:00:41.42,Default,K,0,0,0,,Oh? Who's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.42,0:00:45.75,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,She's chief editor of our company's \Nrestauranteur magazine, Gourmet-Goo...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.75,0:00:47.81,Bengoshi-Top,Natsuko,0,0,0,,My name is Yukawa Natsuko.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.82,0:00:48.59,Bengoshi-Credits_Left,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}This episode's client: \NYukawa Natsuko
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.81,0:00:50.84,Bengoshi-Top,Sara,0,0,0,,She's the one filled with anger...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.84,0:00:51.22,Default,K,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.22,0:00:53.60,Default,Natsuko,0,0,0,,Are you Nonomura-sensei, \Nthe manga illustrator?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.60,0:00:54.47,Default,K,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.47,0:00:56.33,Default,K,0,0,0,,What can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.33,0:01:00.36,Default,Natsuko,0,0,0,,I want to meet the actual protagonist\N of the manga, the lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.36,0:01:01.37,Default,K,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.91,0:01:03.84,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Window_Sign,Words,0,0,0,,Hakamada Law Office
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.45,0:01:06.74,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I'm chief editor of Tokiwa publishing's\N Gourmet-Goo, Yukawa Natsuko.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.74,0:01:08.23,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,I'm Hakamada, attorney at law.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.74,0:01:09.35,Bengoshi-Credits,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Attorney:\N Hakamada Yukio
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.23,0:01:09.35,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,Please come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.35,0:01:12.13,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I'm an avid reader of \NNonomura-sensei's manga.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.13,0:01:15.20,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I'm always impressed by\N the gallant way the lawyer
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.20,0:01:17.35,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,sues for compensation, so this \Ntime, I want a consultation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.35,0:01:21.99,Default,N,0,0,0,,Sensei is only a model \Nfor that protagonist.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.99,0:01:24.29,Default,H,0,0,0,,So, what can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.90,0:01:29.01,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I want to report them.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.60,0:01:30.90,Bengoshi-Marriage_Society,Pamphlet words,0,0,0,,Number one in matchmaking
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.01,0:01:30.61,Default,H,0,0,0,,"Get-Marriage"?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.61,0:01:32.06,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,It's a marriage consultation firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.06,0:01:36.34,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I'm a registered in the 40,000 yen \Nper month premium member course.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.34,0:01:38.24,Bengoshi-Top,Rina,0,0,0,,40,000? Expensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.34,0:01:38.61,Bengoshi-Credits,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Temp:\N Shinozuka Rina
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.24,0:01:39.98,Bengoshi-Top,Nat,0,0,0,,It's been ten months since I enrolled.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.98,0:01:43.55,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,At the end of every week, Get-Marriage \Nhosts a marriage interview party.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.55,0:01:45.39,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I've attended every one,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.39,0:01:47.18,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,and have had over fifty\N interviews with potential partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.18,0:01:48.52,Default,N,0,0,0,,Fifty times?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.52,0:01:52.02,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,But, I haven't found a {\i1}single{\i0}\Nmarriage prospect yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.28,0:01:54.42,Default,H,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.42,0:01:58.72,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I have never neglected \Nmy womanly endeavors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.72,0:02:01.17,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I'm conscientious about \Nbeauty and fashion,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.17,0:02:04.50,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,my income is higher than men of my age,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.50,0:02:07.05,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,and yet I can't find a man to marry.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.05,0:02:09.30,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,That's because this marriage \Nconsultation firm is incompetent!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.71,0:02:14.34,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Therefore...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.34,0:02:17.79,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I want to sue them for all \Nmembership dues I've paid,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.79,0:02:19.35,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,and for compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.35,0:02:21.85,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,That's just a minor complaint—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.36,0:02:27.32,Default,H,0,0,0,,Do you have the \Nmembership contract form?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.32,0:02:28.24,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.38,0:02:30.72,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.92,0:02:32.99,Bengoshi-Contract_Form,Letter,0,0,0,,Membership Contract Form
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.35,0:02:40.27,Default,H,0,0,0,,Based on what I see here, \Nwe might have difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.27,0:02:41.74,Default,N,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.74,0:02:45.08,Default,H,0,0,0,,It says here in the clause that\N there will be no refund in the event
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.08,0:02:48.34,Default,H,0,0,0,,a marriage partner is not found.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.34,0:02:49.94,Default,H,0,0,0,,We don't have a claim to make.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.56,0:02:52.00,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Claim?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.00,0:02:55.07,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Are you saying I'm just making a claim?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:57.25,Default,H,0,0,0,,Well, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.25,0:02:59.60,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Sensei, you're no different from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.60,0:03:00.91,Default,H,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.91,0:03:05.34,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I spoke to the representative of\N Get-Marriage concerning my situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.34,0:03:08.17,Bengoshi-Flashback_Top,Oz,0,0,0,,This is not the fault of our services.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.96,0:03:09.83,Bengoshi-Credits_Left,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Get-Marriage representative:\N Ozaki Masashi
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.49,0:03:11.57,Bengoshi-Flashback_Top,Oz,0,0,0,,But, if you want to lay blame...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.65,0:03:19.44,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Sensei, you're also saying it's my fault \Nthat I can't find a partner, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.44,0:03:21.27,Default,H,0,0,0,,Um... Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.27,0:03:26.40,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I want to meet a man, fall \Nin love, and get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.40,0:03:29.75,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,But I'm no beauty, so my\N chances are slim.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.75,0:03:32.55,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I have no choice but to rely on \Na marriage consultation firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.19,0:03:36.08,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,But, those people take\N advantage of our weaknesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.08,0:03:38.07,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,and rake in membership fees.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.07,0:03:39.73,Default,H,0,0,0,,Well, yes, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.73,0:03:40.59,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.59,0:03:43.13,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Let's take on this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.50,0:03:47.33,Default,N,0,0,0,,Kurumi-san. When did you get here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.33,0:03:50.82,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,A marriage consultation firm \Nlike this ought to be punished.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.82,0:03:52.41,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.41,0:03:55.52,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I am a freelance investigator, \NUmemoto Kurumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.87,0:04:00.31,Bengoshi-Credits_Left,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Freelance investigator: \NUmemoto Kurumi
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.18,0:04:00.68,Bengoshi-Top,Kur,0,0,0,,I will accept your request to \Ninvestigate, for a discounted fee.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.68,0:04:02.25,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.69,0:04:06.65,Default,H,0,0,0,,However, seeing as they \N{\i1}do{\i0} have this clause...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.68,0:04:09.15,Default,H,0,0,0,,This case will be difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.15,0:04:12.73,Default,H,0,0,0,,We would have to prove that the \Nmarriage consultation firm
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.73,0:04:15.81,Default,H,0,0,0,,is purposefully preventing \Nyou from finding a partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.81,0:04:18.09,Default,N,0,0,0,,Which means what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.09,0:04:20.77,Default,H,0,0,0,,That their scheme is to keep \Nbilling for membership
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.20,0:04:24.29,Default,H,0,0,0,,while setting up its members \Nwith mismatched partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.29,0:04:27.87,Default,H,0,0,0,,Or, perhaps the matched \Npartners are hired fakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.87,0:04:31.09,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I can easily find evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.09,0:04:33.44,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Sensei, will you take this client on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.53,0:04:38.00,Default,H,0,0,0,,No, my specialty is divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.00,0:04:41.45,Default,H,0,0,0,,I have no experience in compensation \Nlawsuits against corporations.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.45,0:04:43.09,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Don't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.09,0:04:46.09,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Sensei, your specialty in the past \Nwas corporate law, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.09,0:04:47.76,Default,N,0,0,0,,What, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.76,0:04:49.34,Default,H,0,0,0,,Well, concerning that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.34,0:04:51.44,Default,Y,0,0,0,,He was quite outstanding,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.44,0:04:54.34,Default,Y,0,0,0,,he fought tooth and nail \Nagainst corporations.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.34,0:04:55.60,Default,N,0,0,0,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.60,0:04:57.60,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Then what's the problem, Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.60,0:04:58.59,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.59,0:05:00.39,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I will pay you handsomely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.37,0:05:03.40,Bengoshi-Credits,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Office landlord:\N Toyama Yoshie
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.39,0:05:03.64,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,You don't have anything else to \Ndo anyway, do you, Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.37,0:05:08.83,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I will go all out on this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.83,0:05:11.24,Default,H,0,0,0,,You don't have to display \Nyour enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.24,0:05:12.27,Default,N,0,0,0,,You really don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.27,0:05:13.95,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,No, I want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.68,0:05:23.78,Bengoshi-Title,Title,0,0,0,,Divorce Chaser\N{\fs25}~Let's Turn Your Tears into Money~
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.12,0:05:28.96,Bengoshi-Ep_Title,Right caption,0,0,0,,Divorce Chaser Episode 7 \NInfiltrate the Suspicious Marriage Consultation Firm!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.60,0:05:32.52,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Let me know what day you're going \Nto the marriage consultation firm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.52,0:05:34.70,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I'll be going with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.43,0:05:40.79,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Kurumi-chan is all fired up.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.79,0:05:42.35,Default,K,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.35,0:05:45.95,Default,K,0,0,0,,I've never seen her so insistent \Nabout a client before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.95,0:05:48.88,Default,Y,0,0,0,,I understand how she feels, sort of.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.88,0:05:50.91,Default,K,0,0,0,,Meaning?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.91,0:05:52.12,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.66,0:05:55.14,Default,K,0,0,0,,Who's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.14,0:05:57.42,Default,Y,0,0,0,,That's Kurumi-chan. From four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.41,0:05:59.66,Default,K,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.62,0:06:02.79,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,Before she became an investigator,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.73,0:06:06.23,Bengoshi-Timestamp,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,500)}4 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.79,0:06:06.00,Bengoshi-Top,Y,0,0,0,,she was a regular salaried \Nemployee of a commerce company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.00,0:06:07.07,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,Kurumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.20,0:06:10.57,Bengoshi-4_Years,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}Umemoto Kurumi (4 years ago)
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.71,0:06:10.70,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kurumi,0,0,0,,Oh, Yohei! Are you done, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.70,0:06:12.97,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,Yeah, let's go home together.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.97,0:06:15.36,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Y,0,0,0,,She had a lover who worked \Nat the same company.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.36,0:06:17.01,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Y,0,0,0,,They were virtually living together,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.01,0:06:20.11,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Y,0,0,0,,and were even discussing marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.52,0:06:21.95,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Y,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.95,0:06:24.02,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,You're being transferred\N to the Osaka branch?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.53,0:06:25.93,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,For how long?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.71,0:06:29.06,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,The company says for six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.06,0:06:30.67,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,Six months...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.47,0:06:33.58,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,This is a good opportunity for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.07,0:06:36.57,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,But, I'm making a promise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.16,0:06:40.23,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.23,0:06:42.22,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,When I come back to Tokyo,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.22,0:06:43.56,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,let's get married.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.54,0:06:45.99,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,Yohei...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.27,0:06:51.90,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Yohei,0,0,0,,That's how their six-month \Nlong-distance relationship started.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.26,0:06:55.28,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,Hello, Yohei?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.28,0:06:57.44,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,Today's your birthday, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.44,0:06:59.77,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,Sorry, I'm still at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.45,0:07:08.52,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Y,0,0,0,,Kurumi-chan doesn't act like it, \Nbut she doesn't like being alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.52,0:07:12.90,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Y,0,0,0,,I think the stress of the long-distance \Nrelationship took a toll on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.90,0:07:16.23,Bengoshi-Flashback,Recording,0,0,0,,We cannot answer your call right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.23,0:07:19.81,Bengoshi-Flashback,Recording,0,0,0,,Please leave a message at the beep.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.48,0:07:37.62,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,Kurumi, I'm home.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.39,0:07:37.62,Bengoshi-Timestamp,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Six months later
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.85,0:07:41.76,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,Yohei! Welcome home!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.26,0:07:45.01,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.01,0:07:47.85,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,What do you mean? It's me, Kurumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.25,0:07:49.77,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,The marriage is off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.77,0:07:50.99,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.99,0:07:53.21,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,You said we'd get married \Nwhen you came back to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.21,0:07:55.40,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,Look at your body. \NHow can you speak of marriage?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.40,0:07:57.38,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,Have you looked in the mirror lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.38,0:07:58.06,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,Give the ring back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.06,0:07:59.15,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,Hey, what are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.15,0:07:59.69,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,Give it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.69,0:08:01.80,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,Stop it! Ow, that hurts!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.45,0:08:07.89,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,Y,0,0,0,,It was quite the shock to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.46,0:08:15.91,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Someone who was once so kind to her
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.91,0:08:20.57,Default,Y,0,0,0,,changed completely just because \Nher appearance changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.93,0:08:22.43,Default,N,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.90,0:08:24.10,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.72,0:08:30.75,Default,Y,0,0,0,,She can't forgive people who disparage \N other people's appearances.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.10,0:08:39.89,Bengoshi-Top,Oz,0,0,0,,I'm the representative of \NGet-Marriage, Ozaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.89,0:08:43.02,Bengoshi-Top,T,0,0,0,,I'm Yukawa-sama's assistant, Tachibana.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.25,0:08:43.02,Bengoshi-Credits_Left,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}Natsuko's assistant:\N Tachibana Tetsu
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.02,0:08:45.18,Default,H,0,0,0,,I'm Hakamada, attorney at law.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.18,0:08:46.66,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Please, have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.10,0:08:50.56,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Well, this is quite a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.56,0:08:52.79,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,You even hired an attorney.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.79,0:08:54.23,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.23,0:08:58.67,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I intend to clearly expose \Nyour wrongdoings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.67,0:09:00.32,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,That's unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.32,0:09:05.34,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Our Get-Marriage has the number one\N success rate in the matchmaking industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.34,0:09:08.80,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,We have extremely high rates\N of customer satisfaction.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.80,0:09:13.53,Default,T,0,0,0,,We have introduced many\N partners to Yukawa-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.53,0:09:16.48,Default,T,0,0,0,,Every one of them had \Noutstanding personal backgrounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.48,0:09:19.38,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,But, I haven't found a partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.74,0:09:22.49,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Are you hiring planted fakes to keep \Ncollecting membership dues?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.49,0:09:25.25,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Our company would never\N do anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.25,0:09:28.47,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,The law is very strict \Nabout such things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.47,0:09:32.86,Default,T,0,0,0,,Also, Yukawa-sama has \Nnot been satisfied,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.86,0:09:36.03,Default,T,0,0,0,,so we have repeatedly recommended\N that she cancel her membership.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.03,0:09:37.81,Default,H,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.81,0:09:39.25,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Well, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.25,0:09:42.29,Default,T,0,0,0,,If her dues were all that we wanted,\N we wouldn't have done that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.29,0:09:47.88,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,We have done our utmost to satisfy \NYukawa-sama's demands.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.88,0:09:51.66,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,But, as to why she cannot \Nfind a partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.66,0:09:54.07,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,well, the cause must lie elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.07,0:09:55.29,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Just a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.29,0:09:58.28,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,You want to lay the \Nblame on Natsuko-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.28,0:09:59.26,Default,H,0,0,0,,Kurumi-san, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.26,0:10:01.93,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,I never said that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.33,0:10:05.00,Default,T,0,0,0,,I think Yukawa-sama is \Na magnificent woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.00,0:10:07.36,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Let me ask you, Mr. Assistant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.36,0:10:09.19,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Are you married?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.74,0:10:11.37,Default,T,0,0,0,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.37,0:10:15.67,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,How does a person who's never been \Nmarried assist in matchmaking?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.67,0:10:16.47,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.47,0:10:19.80,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,These men don't \Nunderstand women at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.80,0:10:21.14,Default,H,0,0,0,,Yukawa-san, please—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.14,0:10:23.36,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Your necktie and shirt \Ncombos are always
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.36,0:10:24.86,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,hideously mismatched!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.86,0:10:26.88,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Yellow necktie and blue shirt?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.88,0:10:28.64,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,No sensibility!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.64,0:10:31.92,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,And look at you, with \Nthose smarmy rings.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.92,0:10:34.89,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Are you flaunting the money \Nyou gouged from your members?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.89,0:10:36.32,Default,H,0,0,0,,Both of you, please calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.32,0:10:37.58,Default,H,0,0,0,,Kanae-san, take them outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.58,0:10:39.17,Default,K,0,0,0,,Yes, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.17,0:10:41.66,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,What? We didn't say anything wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.66,0:10:43.00,Default,K,0,0,0,,This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.96,0:10:46.91,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,I find their comments offensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.91,0:10:49.67,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Perhaps I could counter \Nsue them for slander?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.54,0:10:52.24,Default,H,0,0,0,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.69,0:10:56.55,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Well, I don't want matters \Nto get out of hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.55,0:10:58.82,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,We will ask for Yukawa-sama\N to cancel her membership,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.82,0:11:03.45,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,and refund half of her membership fees.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.45,0:11:04.95,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Do we have a deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.29,0:11:08.10,Default,H,0,0,0,,Please let me discuss it with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.53,0:11:12.03,Default,T,0,0,0,,Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.00,0:11:16.44,Default,T,0,0,0,,Do you think we're in the clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.06,0:11:20.33,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Get rid of our list.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.97,0:11:23.24,Default,T,0,0,0,,The "planted" list?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.84,0:11:25.87,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,I wouldn't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.67,0:11:32.86,Default,T,0,0,0,,That lanky, frumpy lawyer doesn't \Nhave the means to investigate us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.35,0:11:36.68,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Window_Sign2,Letters,0,0,0,,Hakamada Law Office
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.92,0:11:37.96,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Half of all the dues I've paid?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.96,0:11:40.90,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I won't settle for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.90,0:11:43.01,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,What's the point of \Nbeing your client,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.01,0:11:45.46,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,if she was going to settle for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.77,0:11:50.16,Default,H,0,0,0,,Considering the circumstances, \NI don't think that's a bad deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.16,0:11:52.47,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,It's not like you to say \Nsuch things, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.47,0:11:55.09,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,You're a compensation lawsuit \Nspecialist, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.09,0:11:58.66,Default,H,0,0,0,,As I said, I'm a {\i1}divorce {\i0}specialist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.66,0:12:01.32,Default,H,0,0,0,,Anyway, based on the current situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.91,0:12:04.59,Default,H,0,0,0,,it would be difficult to \Nsue them for compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.59,0:12:06.01,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.01,0:12:06.67,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.67,0:12:07.85,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.85,0:12:09.48,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,We'll do something about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.48,0:12:12.54,Default,H,0,0,0,,Kurumi-san, please don't take \Nmatters into your own hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.54,0:12:14.13,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I have an idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.13,0:12:15.81,Default,N,0,0,0,,What idea?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.81,0:12:17.81,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Infiltration.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.23,0:12:25.70,Bengoshi-Marriage_Party,Sign,0,0,0,,Marriage interview\N party
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.43,0:12:30.58,Default,M,0,0,0,,Okay! The three minutes are up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.58,0:12:32.56,Default,M,0,0,0,,Now, gentlemen,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.56,0:12:37.45,Default,M,0,0,0,,please take your profile cards \Nand move to the adjacent seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.04,0:12:40.01,Default,M,0,0,0,,As quickly as possible, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.89,0:12:43.25,Default,N,0,0,0,,How did I get roped into this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.48,0:12:48.08,Default,M,0,0,0,,Speed dating, round two.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.08,0:12:50.37,Default,M,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.86,0:12:53.86,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I'm Umemoto Kurumi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.86,0:12:55.43,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I work as a researcher.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.43,0:12:57.60,Default,K,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.60,0:13:00.30,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Lately, I've been addicted\N to a foreign drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.30,0:13:01.94,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Do you know it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.94,0:13:04.44,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,"Iron Spy Woman: Marilyn."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.44,0:13:06.71,Default,Marilyn,0,0,0,,There is no target I can't blow away.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.71,0:13:09.04,Default,Marilyn,0,0,0,,Your heart is no exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.40,0:13:13.27,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Your heart is no exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.15,0:13:17.06,Default,K,0,0,0,,I don't watch dramas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.06,0:13:19.15,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.99,0:13:23.71,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I've spotted one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.71,0:13:26.22,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,This guy is a planted fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.22,0:13:29.59,Bengoshi-Daisuke_Profile,Profile card,0,0,0,,Name: Kawajiri Daisuke\N Age: 33\N Height: 171\N Highest education: Keimei Central University\N Profession: Private Medical Practice
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.61,0:13:28.20,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Keimei graduate, private \Nmedical practitioner.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.20,0:13:29.59,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Annual income of 200,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.59,0:13:32.22,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,His profile would be \Nattractive to women,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.22,0:13:34.77,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,but he doesn't seem\Ninterested in marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.57,0:13:42.44,Default,M,0,0,0,,Okay! Our three minutes are up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.44,0:13:46.03,Default,M,0,0,0,,Gentlemen, please move to adjacent seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.44,0:13:49.68,Bengoshi-Daisuke_Profile,Profile card,0,0,0,,{\3c&H6E696A&\c&H2A282D&}Name: Nonomura Kanae\N Age: 32\N Height: 162\N Highest education: College graduate\N Profession: Manga illustrator
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.44,0:13:50.50,Default,K,0,0,0,,Wow, you're a manga illustrator?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.95,0:13:52.72,Default,K,0,0,0,,I admire creative people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.72,0:13:54.68,Default,N,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.68,0:13:56.47,Default,K,0,0,0,,I've been addicted to this drama lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.47,0:13:58.39,Default,K,0,0,0,,Its original manga is very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.39,0:14:00.78,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,He said he didn't watch dramas!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.78,0:14:04.10,Default,K,0,0,0,,I think manga authors are sublime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.44,0:14:07.42,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,By the way, she's got \None strike already.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.42,0:14:08.27,Default,N,0,0,0,,What? Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.27,0:14:09.15,Default,K,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.87,0:14:14.34,Default,K,0,0,0,,Oh, I admire people \Nwho have life experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.24,0:14:17.97,Default,K,0,0,0,,I've been speed dating \Nlike this for years...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.52,0:14:20.29,Default,K,0,0,0,,but of all the women \NI've interviewed with,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.29,0:14:22.17,Default,K,0,0,0,,you're the most wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.27,0:14:25.17,Default,Hirota,0,0,0,,Are you for real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.17,0:14:26.61,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.61,0:14:28.29,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,That must be a plant.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.73,0:14:33.59,Default,H,0,0,0,,I-I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.49,0:14:36.95,Default,N,0,0,0,,Hakamada-sensei is participating, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.95,0:14:38.91,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I had to twist his arm, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.91,0:14:40.86,Default,Hirota,0,0,0,,You mumble, you don't \Nmake eye contact,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.86,0:14:42.91,Default,Hirota,0,0,0,,and all you talk about is bread!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.91,0:14:45.20,Default,Hirota,0,0,0,,Do you really want to marry someone?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.33,0:14:48.94,Default,H,0,0,0,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.27,0:14:55.27,Default,M,0,0,0,,Okay. Gentleman number 6!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.64,0:14:56.94,Default,M,0,0,0,,Iizuka-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.94,0:14:57.92,Default,Iizuka,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.92,0:14:59.41,Default,M,0,0,0,,Lady number 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.41,0:15:00.58,Default,M,0,0,0,,Nojima-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.58,0:15:01.38,Default,Nojima,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.38,0:15:03.10,Default,M,0,0,0,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.50,0:15:08.30,Default,M,0,0,0,,What a happy occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.30,0:15:09.29,Default,M,0,0,0,,How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.29,0:15:12.02,Default,K,0,0,0,,They've paired five couples already.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.02,0:15:15.09,Default,H,0,0,0,,They say they're number one \Nin the matchmaking industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.09,0:15:17.44,Default,H,0,0,0,,Perhaps it's not a scam.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.44,0:15:19.20,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,It's suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.20,0:15:22.84,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,For example, I, an alluring woman,\N have been left out.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.84,0:15:24.79,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,They give the newcomers \Nthe cold shoulder,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.79,0:15:27.57,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,then they try to prolong \Nour membership.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.57,0:15:29.50,Default,M,0,0,0,,Now, on to the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.50,0:15:31.82,Default,M,0,0,0,,Gentleman number 9, Kawajiri-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.82,0:15:33.12,Default,K,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.12,0:15:37.05,Default,M,0,0,0,,Lady number 8, Nonomura-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.05,0:15:38.86,Default,K,0,0,0,,Oh... yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.84,0:15:42.26,Default,M,0,0,0,,Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.26,0:15:44.29,Default,M,0,0,0,,We have yet another couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.24,0:15:49.53,Default,M,0,0,0,,Nonomura-san, how do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.53,0:15:51.99,Default,K,0,0,0,,I never thought I'd be picked.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.99,0:15:53.12,Default,K,0,0,0,,I'm shocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.12,0:15:55.20,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,What annoying modesty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.20,0:15:58.72,Default,M,0,0,0,,We have one more couple left.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.72,0:16:00.47,Default,M,0,0,0,,Let me announce them!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.47,0:16:03.21,Default,M,0,0,0,,First, lady number 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.21,0:16:04.81,Default,M,0,0,0,,Kuramochi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.25,0:16:06.11,Default,Kuramochi,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.11,0:16:08.31,Default,M,0,0,0,,Gentleman number 10.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.31,0:16:10.41,Default,M,0,0,0,,Hakamada-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.94,0:16:12.65,Default,M,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.48,0:16:18.63,Default,M,0,0,0,,Isn't that nice?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.53,0:16:19.93,Bengoshi-Overlap,Kur,0,0,0,,Sensei, too? But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.53,0:16:23.29,Default,M,0,0,0,,Hakamada-san. How do you feel?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.44,0:16:27.41,Default,H,0,0,0,,I want our relationship to be warm,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.41,0:16:29.92,Default,H,0,0,0,,like freshly baked bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.47,0:16:34.57,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,What an annoying analogy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.70,0:16:39.11,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Don't get carried away \Nbecause you got paired.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.11,0:16:41.50,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,This is just an investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.50,0:16:43.05,Default,H,0,0,0,,Of course, I am aware of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.05,0:16:46.41,Default,K,0,0,0,,Kurumi-san, you're the one getting \Ncarried away. You're seriously upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.41,0:16:48.30,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I'm not upset at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.12,0:16:51.90,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Were you satisfied with the \Nmarriage interview party?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.90,0:16:52.99,Default,K,0,0,0,,Ozaki-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.81,0:16:57.01,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Are you trying to infiltrate us?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.01,0:16:59.03,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,I can't say I approve.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.60,0:17:01.91,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,I will pretend this never happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.91,0:17:03.81,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,as long as you never do this again.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.81,0:17:06.50,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,You're making a nuisance \Nof yourselves to our members.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.62,0:17:09.35,Default,H,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.35,0:17:10.71,Default,H,0,0,0,,I apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.82,0:17:23.99,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Outside_Sign,Sign,0,0,0,,Hakamada \NLaw Office
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.52,0:17:24.71,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,How did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.71,0:17:25.72,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Did you get paired?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.72,0:17:27.60,Default,N,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.60,0:17:29.92,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,That's not important.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.92,0:17:33.73,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Sensei, don't get carried away \Nbecause you got paired up, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.73,0:17:35.40,Default,H,0,0,0,,I'm not getting carried away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.40,0:17:37.57,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Sensei was paired?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.57,0:17:38.85,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,That's too weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.85,0:17:44.62,Default,H,0,0,0,,I think we shouldn't investigate \NGet-Marriage directly for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.62,0:17:47.04,Default,H,0,0,0,,President Ozaki warned us, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.04,0:17:50.58,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,They're definitely suspicious, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.58,0:17:51.87,Default,H,0,0,0,,Indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.87,0:17:54.33,Default,H,0,0,0,,They are on the lookout for us,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.33,0:17:57.03,Default,H,0,0,0,,so there's a high probability \Nthey've got something to hide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.03,0:17:59.59,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,That's where my investigation comes in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.60,0:18:02.42,Default,H,0,0,0,,This case pertains to my client.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.42,0:18:05.06,Default,H,0,0,0,,Please follow my instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.39,0:18:09.00,Default,H,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.82,0:18:11.11,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.11,0:18:13.41,Default,H,0,0,0,,The lady I was coupled with.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.41,0:18:16.28,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,You even exchanged phone numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.28,0:18:17.57,Default,H,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.37,0:18:20.23,Default,H,0,0,0,,It was nice meeting you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.22,0:18:22.57,Default,H,0,0,0,,Tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.13,0:18:24.37,Default,H,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.37,0:18:25.96,Default,H,0,0,0,,I'm not busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.96,0:18:28.75,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,They're going on a date\Nright off the bat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:31.04,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,You see? He got carried away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.14,0:18:36.16,Default,K,0,0,0,,Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.16,0:18:39.42,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Well, Kanae-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.42,0:18:41.05,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Could that be your partner?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.05,0:18:42.48,Default,K,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.48,0:18:47.58,Default,K,0,0,0,,But, I'm going to properly explain \Nmy situation, and turn him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.48,0:18:50.98,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:51.94,Default,K,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.94,0:18:54.01,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Your partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.01,0:18:56.48,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Didn't he say he was\Na long-time member?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.36,0:19:03.93,Default,K,0,0,0,,I was only participating in the \Nspeed-dating party for research.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.93,0:19:05.84,Default,K,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.84,0:19:07.69,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.35,0:19:11.10,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,But you {\i1}are{\i0} single, \Naren't you, Kanae-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.10,0:19:12.84,Default,K,0,0,0,,Well, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.84,0:19:15.03,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,Even if it was just research,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.03,0:19:17.64,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,we've still managed\N to meet each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.40,0:19:21.76,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,Please date me, \Nwith an eye toward marriage!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.76,0:19:23.04,Default,K,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.04,0:19:25.20,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,I don't care if you've got one strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.20,0:19:26.87,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,I will embrace your past, \Nand love you and the whole package—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.87,0:19:28.02,Default,K,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.82,0:19:30.51,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Please give up on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.51,0:19:31.51,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.51,0:19:35.96,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I'm here today because I want you \Nto tell me about Get-Marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.96,0:19:37.51,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,What do you want to know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.51,0:19:40.87,Default,K,0,0,0,,Have you ever been \Ndissatisfied by them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.74,0:19:44.09,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,They're very considerate.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.09,0:19:47.33,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,I'm registered with other \Nmatchmaking establishments,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.33,0:19:50.33,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,but in comparison to the others, \Nthey're warm and accommodating.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.33,0:19:52.88,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Have you ever suspected \Nthey might have planted fakes?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.88,0:19:54.53,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,I don't believe there's \Nanything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.53,0:19:58.17,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,I've always gotten legitimate \Nresponses from matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.59,0:20:01.31,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,Oh, but come to think of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.31,0:20:04.05,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,there was this one time \NI got turned down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.05,0:20:05.04,Default,K,0,0,0,,By whom?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.58,0:20:08.81,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,She's the chief editor \Nof a gourmet magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.81,0:20:10.55,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,This was Yukawa Natsuko-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.55,0:20:12.55,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,That might've been her name—
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.55,0:20:15.94,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,And who was the assistant at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.94,0:20:18.15,Default,Kawajiri,0,0,0,,His name was Tachibana-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.54,0:20:39.24,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Window_Sign3,Sign,0,0,0,,Hakamada Law Office
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.54,0:20:39.24,Default,K,0,0,0,,You were being followed?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.24,0:20:41.45,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Did you get a look at him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.13,0:20:44.77,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I could only see his back,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.77,0:20:46.88,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,so I can't be sure who he was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.57,0:20:52.03,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,But I think that it was \NTachibana-san of Get-Marriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.03,0:20:53.64,Default,K,0,0,0,,Tachibana-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.64,0:20:57.07,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Actually, this isn't the first \Ntime something like this happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.07,0:20:58.47,Default,H,0,0,0,,Can you explain?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.00,0:21:01.92,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I've been followed several \Ntimes before, on my way home.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.92,0:21:07.35,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,There was a man asking \N about me at a local bar I frequent.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.35,0:21:10.43,Default,H,0,0,0,,You think Tachibana-san \Nhas been doing these things?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.27,0:21:13.03,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,It's very possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.84,0:21:17.64,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,This was the first time I actually \Nsaw him in person, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.19,0:21:20.48,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I wonder what's they're scheming.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.48,0:21:22.52,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,We have testimony from a member
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.52,0:21:27.29,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,that Tachibana-san has been obstructing \NNatsuko-san from finding a partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.29,0:21:29.15,Default,H,0,0,0,,Tachibana-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.15,0:21:33.76,Default,H,0,0,0,,Excuse me for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.63,0:21:37.95,Default,H,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.95,0:21:40.24,Default,H,0,0,0,,I enjoyed the visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.24,0:21:43.20,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,That must be his partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.20,0:21:45.73,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,He's totally immersed \Nin "get married" mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.73,0:21:48.65,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Ah, that's it! Tachibana \Nhas been following
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.65,0:21:51.21,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,and gathering personal \Ninformation about me,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.21,0:21:55.33,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,so he can find a completely \Nmismatched man for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.33,0:21:57.16,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,That is entirely conceivable.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.16,0:22:00.31,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,But, Get-Marriage has \Nover a thousand members.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.31,0:22:05.26,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Would they go to such lengths \Nto scam a single member?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.80,0:22:10.89,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Maybe Tachibana-san has a personal \Ngrudge against Natsuko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.89,0:22:12.59,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Against me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.59,0:22:15.23,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Can you think of some \Nreason why he would?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.41,0:22:17.66,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.08,0:22:19.54,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Not particularly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.39,0:22:24.46,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,A reason why someone would have a \Ngrudge against chief editor Yukawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.46,0:22:25.46,Default,K,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.46,0:22:27.54,Default,K,0,0,0,,Misato-san, you're in the same office.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.54,0:22:30.38,Default,K,0,0,0,,I thought you might know something.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.38,0:22:33.88,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,Well... I can think of many reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.88,0:22:35.56,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,You know her personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.56,0:22:37.10,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,She makes lots of enemies.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.10,0:22:38.39,Default,K,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.91,0:22:42.96,Default,K,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.96,0:22:45.26,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,It's Kurumi. Have you found anything out?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.26,0:22:48.44,Default,K,0,0,0,,I've been speaking with \Nmy editor about her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.44,0:22:49.49,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.49,0:22:52.23,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I investigated Tachibana's history.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.23,0:22:56.44,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,That guy was proprietor of a ramen shop \Nbefore he landed the present job.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.44,0:22:58.93,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,His shop went bust in less than a year,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.93,0:23:00.98,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,and he's been knee-deep in debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.98,0:23:03.47,Default,K,0,0,0,,He's got debts from a ramen shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.47,0:23:05.03,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,A ramen shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.40,0:23:06.78,Default,K,0,0,0,,Does that ring a bell?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.78,0:23:10.03,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,Maybe his shop was featured in an \Narticle in Yukawa's magazine.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.03,0:23:13.94,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,There was a time they had an article \Nwith scathing reviews of ramen shops.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.94,0:23:15.93,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,Maybe his shop got reviewed,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.93,0:23:18.63,Default,Misato,0,0,0,,and that's where his grudge came from.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.63,0:23:20.20,Default,K,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.24,0:23:23.01,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I knew he had a personal grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.01,0:23:26.47,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I'm going to go see Tachibana, \Nand nail him to the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.47,0:23:30.04,Default,K,0,0,0,,Wait, before you do that, we should \Nget Hakamada-sensei's instructions...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.04,0:23:32.51,Default,K,0,0,0,,We were warned by Get-Marriage, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.51,0:23:36.07,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,This iron woman isn't \Nintimidated by warnings.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.79,0:23:41.14,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,I feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.73,0:23:43.92,Default,K,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.92,0:23:48.56,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,I feel a tremendous grudge the \Nman called Tachibana has against
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.56,0:23:51.09,Default,Sara,0,0,0,,the female chief editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.09,0:23:53.89,Default,K,0,0,0,,Yes, but we know that already.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.25,0:24:02.57,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Can I talk to you for a minute?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.55,0:24:06.77,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Do you remember this?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:12.69,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,It's got an article about \Nyour ex-ramen shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.38,0:24:14.95,Bengoshi-Ramen_Yeah_Right,Magazine,0,0,0,,Ramen, \NYeah Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.33,0:24:14.95,Bengoshi-Ramen_Tachibana,Magazine,0,0,0,,"Ramen Tachibana"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.97,0:24:14.95,Bengoshi-Ramen_Evaluation,Magazine,0,0,0,,Evaluation:\N {\c&H4E4636&\3c&HFFFDFB&}Materials\N Noodles\N Soup
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.69,0:24:15.81,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,It's quite a harsh review.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.52,0:24:20.47,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Several months after the publication, \Nyour establishment went under,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.47,0:24:23.57,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,and you were left with an enormous debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.14,0:24:27.04,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,You've had a grudge ever \Nsince, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.04,0:24:30.18,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Against Natsuki-san,\N the author of the article.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.07,0:24:32.90,Default,T,0,0,0,,That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.90,0:24:36.77,Default,T,0,0,0,,My restaurant's business was \Ndeclining way before the article.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.27,0:24:39.17,Default,T,0,0,0,,The article had nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.17,0:24:42.23,Default,T,0,0,0,,My restaurant was destined to close.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.67,0:24:47.03,Default,T,0,0,0,,You could say I'm actually thankful \Nto Yukawa-sama about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.49,0:24:50.22,Default,T,0,0,0,,because that article woke \Nme up to the hard facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.22,0:24:53.83,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Then why are you obstructing \NNatsuko-san's marriage interviews?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.83,0:24:58.09,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I heard you spread bad rumors\N about her to prospective partners.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.17,0:25:03.00,Default,T,0,0,0,,I'm not allowed to discuss \Nproprietary information.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.00,0:25:04.26,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Wait, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.26,0:25:05.91,Default,T,0,0,0,,Please, leave me alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.91,0:25:08.27,Default,T,0,0,0,,Representative Ozaki is \Nstringent about rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.27,0:25:09.91,Default,T,0,0,0,,If he found out I relayed \Nproprietary information,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.91,0:25:11.66,Default,T,0,0,0,,or that I got involved with a member,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.66,0:25:15.91,Default,T,0,0,0,,I'd be quickly fired, and \Nforced to pay 15 million yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.91,0:25:18.58,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,We know you've been following \NNatsuko-san around!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.06,0:25:25.08,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,What would you do if \Nthat fact got publicized?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.70,0:25:27.95,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,I think that's enough of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.68,0:25:32.66,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,I warned you to stop \Nsniffing around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.30,0:25:35.99,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Who are you calling?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.41,0:25:37.99,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,The police.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.22,0:25:43.65,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Your actions are no \Ndifferent from blackmail.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.04,0:25:49.68,Default,H,0,0,0,,I told you not to do reckless\N investigations, did I not?!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.07,0:25:54.55,Default,H,0,0,0,,I got a serious warning \Nfrom the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.99,0:25:56.55,Default,H,0,0,0,,One more wrong move,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.55,0:25:58.68,Default,H,0,0,0,,and you could have been arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.48,0:26:01.65,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,But, we need to find a way to win—
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.65,0:26:05.49,Default,H,0,0,0,,Win or lose, that's my responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.18,0:26:08.93,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Because of what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.93,0:26:12.13,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Get-Marriage will \Ntighten their security.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.82,0:26:16.27,Default,H,0,0,0,,Now it will be harder than\N ever to gather evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.10,0:26:23.32,Default,H,0,0,0,,You have worsened circumstances \Nconsiderably for our client.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.89,0:26:28.63,Default,H,0,0,0,,Please cease your \Ninvolvement with this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.40,0:26:34.86,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.84,0:26:41.82,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Um... here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.66,0:26:46.27,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I recorded my conversation \Nwith Tachibana.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.27,0:26:48.67,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I was hoping it might be of some use.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.77,0:26:55.67,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.23,0:27:02.41,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Let's go out for drinks. \NIt's happy time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.41,0:27:03.65,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Marilyn.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.80,0:27:05.97,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.65,0:27:09.02,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Was there a fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.02,0:27:10.75,Default,K,0,0,0,,Yes. Somewhat.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.69,0:27:19.15,Default,Y,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.15,0:27:21.23,Default,Y,0,0,0,,Kurumi-chan overdid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.23,0:27:24.87,Default,K,0,0,0,,I've never seen \NHakamada-sensei get so angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.72,0:27:31.89,Default,Y,0,0,0,,She must've grown impatient with \NHakamada-sensei's procedures.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.89,0:27:33.34,Default,K,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.18,0:27:40.12,Default,Y,0,0,0,,There's more to the story\N of Kurumi-chan's dissolved engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.65,0:27:46.19,Bengoshi-Timestamp,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,360)}4 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.70,0:27:50.53,Bengoshi-Flashback,Y,0,0,0,,Umemoto-san, time to \Npay this month's rent.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.53,0:27:51.83,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,Ms. Landlord...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.40,0:27:56.89,Bengoshi-Flashback,Y,0,0,0,,Are you still sniveling about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.42,0:28:02.46,Bengoshi-Flashback,Y,0,0,0,,I'll introduce you to \Nsomeone really nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.46,0:28:03.60,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.95,0:28:07.63,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,I understand the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.89,0:28:10.98,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,Please leave the rest to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.98,0:28:13.71,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,Oh. The rice is ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.35,0:28:19.80,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,Would you like to eat before you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.80,0:28:21.29,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,It's freshly mixed rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.29,0:28:22.96,Default,K,0,0,0,,Mixed rice?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.96,0:28:24.93,Default,Y,0,0,0,,At that time, Hakamada-sensei
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.93,0:28:27.83,Default,Y,0,0,0,,was into mixed rice, and not bread.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.83,0:28:29.71,Default,K,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.12,0:28:32.83,Default,H,0,0,0,,And what Hakamada-sensei \Ndid for her after that...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.83,0:28:34.85,Default,H,0,0,0,,was splendid.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.68,0:28:43.33,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,In other words, you're saying \NUmemoto-san is entirely at fault
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.33,0:28:45.78,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,for the engagement dissolving, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.68,0:28:48.48,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.48,0:28:51.69,Bengoshi-Flashback,Yohei,0,0,0,,How could I marry an \Nunsightly thing like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.99,0:28:54.86,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,I wonder if that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.05,0:29:04.93,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,Here's evidence you were cheating \Non her during your stint in Osaka.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.48,0:29:09.84,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,I know I'm overstepping \Nmy bounds, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.81,0:29:13.02,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,before you disparage \Npeople's appearances,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.02,0:29:15.57,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,you ought to reflect \Non your own actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.80,0:29:21.62,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,We're suing for one million yen,\N for breach of engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.25,0:29:23.85,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,You will pay, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.81,0:29:31.72,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,Umemoto-san, you were \Nlucky this time around.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.72,0:29:32.92,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kur,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.49,0:29:38.61,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,Because you didn't wind \Nup marrying a cheater,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.39,0:29:41.46,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,who shallowly judges people \Nby their appearances.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.60,0:29:58.90,Default,K,0,0,0,,Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.82,0:30:02.69,Default,H,0,0,0,,What can I do for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.69,0:30:07.06,Default,K,0,0,0,,Will you please let Kurumi-san \Ncontinue her investigation?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.70,0:30:11.74,Default,H,0,0,0,,I can't have her getting us \Ninto any more trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.74,0:30:13.77,Default,K,0,0,0,,I heard from Yoshie-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.39,0:30:18.87,Default,K,0,0,0,,Kurumi-san was once your \Nclient, wasn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.67,0:30:22.97,Default,H,0,0,0,,She sure likes to gossip.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.36,0:30:26.34,Default,K,0,0,0,,Kurumi-san put her \Nhopes in you, Sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.58,0:30:29.44,Default,K,0,0,0,,She wanted you to save a client,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.44,0:30:32.65,Default,K,0,0,0,,who suffered like she once did.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.75,0:30:35.73,Default,K,0,0,0,,Maybe it's just me,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.73,0:30:38.61,Default,K,0,0,0,,but you're not yourself this \Ntime around, Hakamada-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.14,0:30:44.39,Default,K,0,0,0,,Maybe you got carried away \Nbecause you've been paired now,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.39,0:30:46.36,Default,K,0,0,0,,but you should consider \Nyour client's feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.36,0:30:48.96,Default,K,0,0,0,,consider her happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.96,0:30:51.04,Default,K,0,0,0,,Isn't that how you always work, Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.76,0:30:58.93,Default,K,0,0,0,,Kurumi-san forced you to \Ntake on this client...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.29,0:31:02.45,Default,K,0,0,0,,because she believed in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.61,0:31:06.33,Default,H,0,0,0,,In that case, I wish
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.33,0:31:08.92,Default,H,0,0,0,,she had kept believing in me, \Njust a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.92,0:31:10.49,Default,K,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.49,0:31:14.68,Default,H,0,0,0,,I haven't gotten carried away \Nin the least.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.13,0:31:19.51,Bengoshi-Internal/Narrator,H,0,0,0,,The reason why I was \Nseeing my partner...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.51,0:31:24.22,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kuramochi,0,0,0,,I see, so you wanted to investigate.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.65,0:31:27.31,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,I'm truly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.31,0:31:31.41,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kuramochi,0,0,0,,No, I'm glad you were honest with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.87,0:31:36.01,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kuramochi,0,0,0,,I've gotten into relationships with \Npartners who stopped calling me,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.01,0:31:40.25,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kuramochi,0,0,0,,or reject me outright without \Ngiving any reason whatsoever...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.14,0:31:42.55,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.18,0:31:45.92,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kuramochi,0,0,0,,A friend of mine recommended \Nthe company to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.92,0:31:48.18,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kuramochi,0,0,0,,I've been a member for two years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.18,0:31:51.39,Bengoshi-Flashback,Kuramochi,0,0,0,,But, it ends the same\N way every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.17,0:31:55.70,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,Would you mind sharing details with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.70,0:31:59.16,Default,Kuramochi,0,0,0,,She gave me references to other members,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.16,0:32:01.14,Default,Kuramochi,0,0,0,,and I spoke with several of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.57,0:32:03.06,Default,H,0,0,0,,Strangely enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.06,0:32:07.39,Default,H,0,0,0,,people's opinions of\N Get-Marriage got split in two.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.39,0:32:09.69,Default,H,0,0,0,,Between those who are completely satisfied,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.69,0:32:10.91,Default,H,0,0,0,,and those who aren't.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.91,0:32:13.18,Default,K,0,0,0,,What's that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.18,0:32:16.55,Default,H,0,0,0,,I think Get-Marriage sorts its members.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.55,0:32:18.72,Default,H,0,0,0,,They're sorted into people \Nwho will aggressively
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.72,0:32:21.92,Default,H,0,0,0,,get paired, in order to \Nraise their success rate...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.92,0:32:23.75,Default,H,0,0,0,,and into people who are scammed,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.75,0:32:25.97,Default,H,0,0,0,,who only get set up with fakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.97,0:32:29.41,Default,K,0,0,0,,If you know that, you can \Nsue them for compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.41,0:32:33.23,Default,H,0,0,0,,The only thing I'm missing \Nis solid evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.23,0:32:34.77,Default,H,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.89,0:32:39.27,Default,H,0,0,0,,thanks to this, I now \Nhave a course of action.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.27,0:32:40.64,Default,K,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.64,0:32:43.06,Default,H,0,0,0,,Please call Kurumi-san for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.06,0:32:45.90,Default,H,0,0,0,,I need her to do further investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.90,0:32:47.38,Default,K,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.11,0:32:51.78,Bengoshi-Eternal_Partners,Poster,0,0,0,,Eternal Partners
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.31,0:32:56.51,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Have you agreed to our \Nterms from the other day?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.88,0:32:57.85,Default,H,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.85,0:33:01.35,Default,H,0,0,0,,We will be suing for a complete refund\N of all membership fees paid,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.35,0:33:03.79,Default,H,0,0,0,,as well as compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.79,0:33:05.07,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.07,0:33:06.93,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Why have you decided that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.38,0:33:14.13,Default,H,0,0,0,,Because you have purposefully obstructed \NNatsuko-san from finding a marriage partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.81,0:33:19.92,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,And what advantage would we have \Nfor doing something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.92,0:33:20.97,Default,H,0,0,0,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.47,0:33:25.59,Default,H,0,0,0,,You've been selecting targets.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.40,0:33:31.22,Default,H,0,0,0,,You pick out people who \Nseem prone to rejection...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.82,0:33:34.79,Default,H,0,0,0,,and to keep raking membership \Nfees from those people,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.79,0:33:37.06,Default,H,0,0,0,,you obstruct them \Nfrom finding a mate.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.15,0:33:40.63,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,That's nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.63,0:33:42.17,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,You have no evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.17,0:33:45.36,Default,H,0,0,0,,True, I don't have evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.36,0:33:49.14,Default,H,0,0,0,,However, there is one thing we know.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.17,0:33:50.81,Default,H,0,0,0,,Tachibana-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.98,0:33:53.04,Default,T,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.04,0:33:58.35,Default,H,0,0,0,,You were obstructing Natsuko-san\N for a personal reason, weren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.65,0:34:01.95,Default,T,0,0,0,,This again?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.95,0:34:03.80,Default,T,0,0,0,,I don't have a grudge
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.80,0:34:06.58,Default,T,0,0,0,,against Yukawa-sama because \Nof that ramen shop article.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.58,0:34:07.76,Default,H,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.76,0:34:11.19,Default,H,0,0,0,,The personal reason isn't a grudge.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.19,0:34:12.69,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.69,0:34:15.96,Default,H,0,0,0,,He is fond of Natsuko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.55,0:34:19.03,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Fond?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.03,0:34:20.88,Default,H,0,0,0,,The first time I noticed,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.88,0:34:23.45,Default,H,0,0,0,,was when she commented \Non your tie and shirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.45,0:34:25.84,Bengoshi-Flashback,Nat,0,0,0,,Your necktie and shirt \Ncombos are always
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.84,0:34:27.28,Bengoshi-Flashback,Nat,0,0,0,,hideously mismatched!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.28,0:34:29.36,Bengoshi-Flashback,Nat,0,0,0,,Yellow necktie and blue shirt?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.36,0:34:31.15,Bengoshi-Flashback,Nat,0,0,0,,No sensibility!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.15,0:34:34.18,Default,H,0,0,0,,A few days after Natsuko-san\N criticized your color combinations,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.18,0:34:37.27,Default,H,0,0,0,,you took her words faithfully to heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.27,0:34:39.46,Default,H,0,0,0,,You changed the color of your tie.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.42,0:34:46.48,Default,H,0,0,0,,Because you are fond of Natsuko-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.48,0:34:49.16,Default,H,0,0,0,,you wanted Natsuko-san for yourself...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.88,0:34:52.37,Default,H,0,0,0,,so you were obstructing her prospects.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.54,0:34:59.08,Default,T,0,0,0,,You can't infer all that \Nfrom the color of my tie.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.08,0:35:01.30,Default,T,0,0,0,,That's no evidence of anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.30,0:35:03.58,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,There's more evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.44,0:35:08.93,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Hey, you, enough is enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.93,0:35:10.84,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,You had fair warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.69,0:35:14.20,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I wasn't investigating you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.65,0:35:16.89,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I found this site.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.66,0:35:19.84,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,The author is anonymous,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.66,0:35:20.83,Bengoshi-Blog_Title,Blog name,0,0,0,,One-sided Confessions of a Matchmaking Firm
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.66,0:35:20.83,Bengoshi-Blog_Entry,Article title,0,0,0,,Even if I only can talk with her \N{\b0\c&H24301C&}(Wednesday)\N She came to our matchmaking firm again today. \NShe makes me happy, even speaking with her face to face. Even at my age, she makes my heart pound.{\b1}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.84,0:35:21.89,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,but it's blog by an employee \Nof a matchmaking firm,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.83,0:35:22.76,Bengoshi-Blog_Entry,Article 2 title,0,0,0,,The joy of meeting with her
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.89,0:35:25.04,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,confessing his secret love for a member.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.76,0:35:24.53,Bengoshi-Blog_Entry,Article 3 title,0,0,0,,A lovely bar
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.04,0:35:26.85,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,It talks about how he follows her home,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.85,0:35:30.02,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,and how he would get information \Nabout her from people in her social circles.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.02,0:35:33.27,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,He's quite passionate about \Nher, as you can see.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.14,0:35:32.50,Bengoshi-Blog_Entry,,0,0,0,,A lovely bar
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.50,0:35:34.27,Bengoshi-Blog_Entry,Article title,0,0,0,,She's like an angel
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.27,0:35:35.97,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,Oh yes, and have a look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.04,0:35:40.45,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,There's even a picture \Nof his secret love.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.92,0:35:47.30,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,It would be easy to find the blogger.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.92,0:35:51.41,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,This is ample evidence, wouldn't \Nyou say, Hakamada-sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.81,0:35:52.95,Default,H,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.95,0:35:56.09,Default,H,0,0,0,,I expect no less from you, \NInvestigator Umemoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.62,0:36:01.22,Default,H,0,0,0,,Tachibana-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.22,0:36:04.24,Default,H,0,0,0,,Isn't it time to tell the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.14,0:36:08.37,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Tachibana-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.37,0:36:10.26,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,I've had enough of you, Tachibana!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.26,0:36:14.60,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Who was it that got \Nyou out of your debt?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.11,0:36:18.49,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Have you forgotten the rules?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.95,0:36:22.69,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Employees that leak proprietary \Ninformation will be penalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.97,0:36:26.45,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,Are you trying to get \Nyourself in debt again?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.53,0:36:30.21,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,Is that the rule that would\N force him to pay 15 million yen?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.93,0:36:33.71,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,He has exposed the illegal \Nactivities of his company,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.71,0:36:36.96,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,and you would penalize him for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.30,0:36:43.44,Bengoshi-Vocab_Word,Caption top,0,0,0,,{\fad(550,550)}Public Well-Being Informant Protection Law
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.30,0:36:43.44,Bengoshi-Vocab_Definition,Caption bottom,0,0,0,,{\fad(550,550)}The law that protects workers who report unethical insider conduct
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.96,0:36:39.48,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,Based on the Public Well-Being \NInformant Protection Law...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.48,0:36:40.54,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,you can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.21,0:36:49.49,Default,T,0,0,0,,Shortly after I joined the company,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.31,0:36:55.31,Default,T,0,0,0,,representative Ozaki gave me a list.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.56,0:37:00.22,Bengoshi-Flashback,T,0,0,0,,The "planted" list...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.06,0:37:02.48,Bengoshi-Flashback,T,0,0,0,,What this?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.05,0:37:08.60,Bengoshi-Flashback,Oz,0,0,0,,It's a list of members who I believe \Nare unlikely to find a partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.60,0:37:09.86,Bengoshi-Flashback,T,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.04,0:37:13.01,Bengoshi-Flashback,Oz,0,0,0,,Set them up with fake "plants,"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.01,0:37:15.92,Bengoshi-Flashback,Oz,0,0,0,,and let them believe \Nthey're getting somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.92,0:37:19.89,Bengoshi-Flashback,Oz,0,0,0,,People like that\N desperately cling to us...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.25,0:37:24.61,Bengoshi-Flashback,Oz,0,0,0,,and they'll keep paying \Nmembership fees for all eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.58,0:37:28.32,Default,K,0,0,0,,How awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.07,0:37:34.54,Default,T,0,0,0,,Yukawa-sama's name was \Non that list, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.12,0:37:36.72,Bengoshi-Yukawa_List,List,0,0,0,,Yukawa Natsuko
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.61,0:37:41.71,Default,T,0,0,0,,I thought I'd happened \Nupon an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.41,0:37:44.33,Default,T,0,0,0,,Because as long as I was setting \Nher up with nothing but fakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.33,0:37:46.77,Default,T,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have to worry about \NYukawa-sama ever getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.67,0:37:52.23,Default,T,0,0,0,,It's true that I have \Nbeen obstructing her.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.68,0:37:56.31,Default,T,0,0,0,,I thought maybe some day \Nshe would go out with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.31,0:37:58.68,Default,K,0,0,0,,You shouldn't have been so devious.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.68,0:38:02.19,Default,K,0,0,0,,Why didn't you just come out and \Nprofess your love to Natsuko-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.19,0:38:04.89,Default,T,0,0,0,,Company rules prohibit relationships with members.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.48,0:38:08.82,Default,T,0,0,0,,I was afraid of being penalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.82,0:38:10.34,Default,T,0,0,0,,That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.74,0:38:13.03,Default,T,0,0,0,,that why after Yukawa-sama resigned,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.89,0:38:19.43,Default,T,0,0,0,,I was going to properly ask her out.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.44,0:38:29.15,Default,H,0,0,0,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.75,0:38:34.11,Default,H,0,0,0,,It's clear you've been scamming\N your members using fakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.45,0:38:38.11,Default,H,0,0,0,,The total membership \Nfees and compensation...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.11,0:38:39.56,Default,H,0,0,0,,You will pay, won't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.64,0:38:43.21,Default,H,0,0,0,,And one more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.83,0:38:44.99,Default,H,0,0,0,,Tachibana-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.99,0:38:49.63,Default,H,0,0,0,,Please inform all members on that list.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.47,0:38:52.33,Default,H,0,0,0,,Like Natsuko-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.00,0:38:55.10,Default,H,0,0,0,,they have fallen victim to a scam.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.19,0:39:01.37,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,If you do that, our company will be ruined!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.37,0:39:03.84,Default,H,0,0,0,,And what's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.32,0:39:07.33,Default,H,0,0,0,,After all, you shallowly judge \Npeople based on appearances...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.86,0:39:10.72,Default,H,0,0,0,,You're not qualified to \Noversee human encounters.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.19,0:39:19.68,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,{\i1}Umemoto-san, you were \Nlucky this time around.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.68,0:39:23.66,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,{\i1}Because you didn't wind \Nup marrying a cheater,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.58,0:39:26.93,Bengoshi-Flashback,H,0,0,0,,who shallowly judges people \Nby their appearances.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.49,0:39:39.89,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,You look like an \Ninsignificant lawyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.49,0:39:45.73,Default,Oz,0,0,0,,but I guess you can't judge \Npeople on appearances.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.26,0:40:02.60,Bengoshi-Hakamada_Window_Sign2,Sign,0,0,0,,Hakamada Law Office
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.60,0:40:07.70,Bengoshi-News_Headline,Paper,0,0,0,,Major corporation Get-Marriage crushed\N{\fs20}Illicit activities toward its members uncovered
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.05,0:40:06.62,Default,Rina,0,0,0,,Wow, the matchmaking firm \Nwent out of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.62,0:40:08.94,Default,K,0,0,0,,That's our Hakamada-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.94,0:40:12.19,Default,K,0,0,0,,He rescued not one, but many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.24,0:40:18.01,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I am truly sorry about how \NI behaved this time around.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.77,0:40:20.28,Default,H,0,0,0,,If you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.28,0:40:23.00,Default,H,0,0,0,,then please do not do reckless \Ninvestigations any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.74,0:40:25.19,Default,Kur,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.92,0:40:28.53,Default,K,0,0,0,,Sensei, we have a guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.53,0:40:29.73,Default,H,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.91,0:40:33.60,Default,H,0,0,0,,Natsuko-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.60,0:40:37.00,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Thank you for everything \Nyou have done for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.65,0:40:38.97,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,You too, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.36,0:40:46.94,Default,T,0,0,0,,Everyone. I have caused \Nyou much trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.94,0:40:48.42,Default,K,0,0,0,,Tachibana-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.42,0:40:49.51,Default,K,0,0,0,,Why are you here, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.45,0:40:54.88,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,Well, we are getting married.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.88,0:40:55.99,Default,All,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.99,0:40:59.59,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,That day, when Tachibana-san \Nconfessed his feelings,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.59,0:41:01.69,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,I couldn't get that out of my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.69,0:41:04.86,Default,Nat,0,0,0,,So I got brave, and called him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.69,0:41:09.22,Default,T,0,0,0,,I brought hardship to many people.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.22,0:41:12.53,Default,T,0,0,0,,For that, I must make amends \Nfor the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.45,0:41:18.39,Default,T,0,0,0,,But, Natsuko-san forgave me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.57,0:41:24.05,Default,T,0,0,0,,I will make her happy, I promise!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.72,0:41:31.53,Bengoshi-Top,Kur,0,0,0,,I'm glad for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.67,0:41:38.03,Bengoshi-Top,Nat,0,0,0,,The compensation we received \Nwill help us make a new start.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.43,0:41:40.82,Bengoshi-Top,Nat,0,0,0,,We cannot thank Sensei enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.92,0:41:46.12,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,If you're going to show gratitude...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.70,0:41:49.78,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,it should be toward her.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.78,0:41:50.70,Bengoshi-Top,Kur,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.70,0:41:54.45,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,We couldn't have sued for compensation
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.45,0:41:56.77,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,without her investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.42,0:42:08.35,Bengoshi-Top,Kur,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, here is the bill \Nfor the case's investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.29,0:42:11.47,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,Can you please wait a little for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.47,0:42:12.89,Bengoshi-Top,Kur,0,0,0,,You said you couldn't have sued for
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.89,0:42:15.26,Bengoshi-Top,Kur,0,0,0,,compensation if it weren't \Nfor my investigation, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.26,0:42:17.42,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,That and this are unrelated...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.42,0:42:19.23,Bengoshi-Top,Kur,0,0,0,,Wait! Grab him!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.23,0:42:20.40,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,Please, don't do this!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.40,0:42:22.67,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,I will pay it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.67,0:42:24.70,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,I promise I'll pay it!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.70,0:42:27.41,Bengoshi-Top,Man,0,0,0,,You're taking the children \Naway from me, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.70,0:42:36.08,Bengoshi-Next_Episode,Caption,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.41,0:42:29.41,Bengoshi-Top,Woman,0,0,0,,He's a pathetic husband \Nwho can't find another job.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.47,0:42:31.61,Bengoshi-End_Splash_Left,Caption,0,0,0,,Childcare worker husband {\c&H3510ED&}VS {\c&HDB77EF&}career-woman wife
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.41,0:42:31.24,Bengoshi-Top,Woman,0,0,0,,So I threatened\N him with a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.24,0:42:32.88,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,The wife admits\N to illicit activity.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.61,0:42:36.08,Bengoshi-End_Splash_Right,Caption,0,0,0,,A mess of a custody battle: \N{\c&H5143E2&}What will happen to the children's {\c&H3EE3D8&}future?!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.88,0:42:34.20,Bengoshi-Top,H,0,0,0,,In which case we can \Nsue for compensation.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.20,0:42:36.08,Bengoshi-Top,Boy,0,0,0,,You're not a \Nsuperhero of justice!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.08,0:42:39.68,Bengoshi-Top,Boy,0,0,0,,You're a villain that's \Nsplitting Mama and Papa apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.25,0:42:39.72,Bengoshi-Fiction,Caption,0,0,0,,{\fad(360,0)}This drama is a work of fiction

